_rawBody:
A tailor makes $x$ dresses and $y$ shirts in one week.
In one week

\begin{parts}
\item he makes at least 4 dresses
\item he makes no more than 7 shirts
\item he makes less than 14 dresses and shirts altogether
\item the number of shirts he makes is more than $\frac{2}{3}$ of the number of dresses.
\end{parts}

One of the inequalities that shows this information is $x \geqslant 4$.

\begin{parts}
\item Write down the other three inequalities in $x$ and/or $y$.

\AnswerLine
\Marks{3}

\item
\begin{center}
\relinput{Figures/Q08b.tex}
\end{center}

On the grid, draw 4 straight lines and shade the unwanted regions to show these inequalities.
Label the region $R$ that satisfies the 4 inequalities.

\Marks{6}

\item Use your diagram to find the smallest number of dresses and the smallest number of shirts the tailor makes in one week.

\AnswerLine[][dresses and ........................... shirts]
\Marks{1}

\item The profit the tailor makes on one dress is \$10 and the profit on one shirt is \$6.

Use your diagram to find the largest profit the tailor can make in one week.

\AnswerLine[\$][]
\Marks{2}

\end{parts}

